modules.description: Provides functions to query jemalloc's control API, retrieve memory allocator statistics, and modify runtime properties. Operates on low-level memory management structures and configuration parameters exposed by jemalloc. Used to monitor memory usage patterns and tune allocation behavior in performance-critical applications.

Provides functions to monitor and control jemalloc's memory behavior, including releasing unused memory, retrieving version details, and querying statistics via mallctl. Works with types like memory_stats and handles operations such as fetching integer, boolean, or string values from jemalloc's control interface. Used to dynamically adjust memory usage and gather detailed runtime metrics for performance tuning.
